The paper deals with the phase retrieval problem, which is a common problem in signal processing and imaging. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is a likely category as it deals with the transmission, processing, and utilization of information. The paper also proposes an algorithm that utilizes sparse priority, which falls under the category of machine learning and optimization. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category. The paper also mentions the use of the algorithm in image processing, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of theoretical analyses to prove the convergence of the algorithm, which falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper mentions the robustness of the algorithm to noise, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI).
